        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1958-06-12T14:10:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1958-06-12T14:10:00-05:00" n="413"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d413">
                <head>413. Memorandum of a Telephone Conversation Between the <gloss type="from"
                        >President</gloss> and the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>,
                    Washington, June 12, 1958, 3:10 p.m.<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d413fn1"
                        >Source: Eisenhower Library, <persName corresp="#p_DAW1">Dulles</persName>
                        Papers, White House Telephone Conversations. No classification marking.
                        Prepared by <persName corresp="#p_BPD1">Phyllis D. Bernau</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" type="conversation-or-meeting-date"
                            when="1958-06-12T15:10:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 12, 1958, 3:10 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Sec returned the call and the Pres said he saw in the paper <persName
                        corresp="#p_GCP1">Garcia</persName> was coming over to urge we pay 800
                    million we owe them. The Pres said we paid until we bled. The Sec replied he is
                    afraid he is coming over for that. The Pres asked why we invited him. The Sec
                    said we have to live with him and we made it clear we would not consider
                    anything of that sort. The Sec also said we are going to have a tough time with
                    him. The Pres said we just say no. OK to make a deal to help him out and we get
                    what we want too. The Sec explained the same trouble we had with Magsaysay.</p>
                <p>[Here follows discussion on reciprocal trade.]</p>
            </div>
